	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName> <date>8 March 1859</date></p>
				<p>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. and Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have delayed until the last moment<lb/> to write in the hope of having something favorable to add&#59; but<lb/> in vain.  There are two or three who partially promise to<lb/> become subscribers if it become a Weekly&#44; but would like to<lb/> see it first and object to paying in advance.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In congregational matters<lb/> all is quiet with us&#44; and I believe likewise with the others<lb/> in some degree.  They are preparing for a second Confirmation<lb/> on <add>Hebrew</add>&#58; I send you herewith one of the Catechisms.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">What I have marked with <hi rend="underline">double lines</hi> is strongly<lb/> objected to by <persName>Pope Gerstle</persName>&#59; but the moderator <persName>Gotthelf</persName><lb/> has satisfied him that it will not do to slash too<lb/> deeply at first.  I need not comment thereon&#44;<lb/> and leave it entirely optional with you to notice the<lb/> choice morceau.  Last year 15 were confirmed&#44; of&#44;<lb/> whom only <hi rend="underline">one</hi> &#40;father and son&#41; observes the <date>Sabbath</date>&#58; so<lb/> much for consistency&#58; and from a knowledge of the<lb/> parties generally&#44; I suspect the new batch will be<lb/> the same.  The &#125; is mine.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I hope soon to have better news&#44; and may<lb/> success attend you in all your praiseworthy exertions is<lb/> the sincere wish of<lb/> Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. and Dear Sir<lb/> Truly Yours</p>
				<p><persName role="author">A. I. H. Bernal</persName></p>
				<p><persName>Mr B.</persName> and <persName>Mr &#38; Mrs Hassan</persName><lb/> present their best respects and<lb/> kind regards.</p>
		</body>
